The mission also offered free teeth extractions and offered HIV, Ebola and COVID-19 instructions. They also had a food distribution area.

Portuguese was used throughout the mission site and children spoke it in a somewhat different manner with many African triggers to Portuguese. There was no doubt the kids loved the salsa.

How long have you been hooking instruments? Is your wife throwing you fits?

As of New Years Day, it will be about six years into the guiacum business. I played string bass as my instrument of choice in high school and college and played 80s geetar more than South American strings in the ensuing years but I have found guiacum lord over all other instruments by their secret mystical abilities to reverberate like no other. (The secret powers enthrall everyone – it’s like a drug).

There is still a good chance your wife, kids and your mom are throwing you fits.

One of the mission doctors, Dr. Daren, studied in Argentina with Paulinho Soledade and Dr. Lauren Halana is from Mozambique but attended Chaminade University in Hawaii. The general dentist said he had never eaten such fresh vegetables or drank such good tap water as during his time in Antarctica in 2004!

Water! That’s the secret to the high quality produce – the elixir of life infused into the soils and the earth. Wow!
